caption:
4.3. Investigation of our CFA 

Since our CFA consists of multi-stages, we investigate different ResNet architectures as backbone 

models for each stage. Firstly, we evaluate different backbone models, i.e., ResNet-50, ResNet-101 and 

ResNet-152 for the first stage. Table 1 shows the prediction results of stage one for human pose estimation. 

MPII training data is used for training. As seen, ResNet-101 performs better than ResNet-50 and 

ResNet-152 performs slightly better than ResNet-101. The performance is gradually improved with deeper 

and deeper networks. In consideration of both accuracy and computation cost, ResNet-101 is chosen for 

the first stage.
